# Testing Conventions

## Naming
- Classes: `*Test` (unit), `*IntegrationTest` (integration)
- Methods: descriptive behavior — `shouldReturnNotFoundWhenMissing`
- `@Nested` for grouping related scenarios
- `@TestInstance(TestInstance.Lifecycle.PER_CLASS)` for shared state

## Unit Test Structure
```java
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class OrderServiceTest {
    @Mock private OrderDal dal;
    @Mock private EventPublisher publisher;
    @InjectMocks private OrderService service;

    @Nested
    class WhenCreatingOrder {
        @Test
        void shouldPersistAndPublishEvent() { }
    }
}
```

## Spring Boot Tests
```java
@SpringBootTest
@ContextConfiguration(classes = {ServiceUnderTest.class, Dependencies.class})
@TestPropertySource(properties = {"config.key=testValue"})
class MySpringTest {
    @Autowired private ServiceUnderTest service;
    @MockBean private ExternalDependency dependency;
}
```
- H2 in-memory database (auto-configured)
- `@DirtiesContext` when context is modified

## Embedded Kafka
```java
@EmbeddedKafka
@ResourceLock("embeddedKafkaResource")
class KafkaIntegrationTest { }
```

## Frameworks
- **JUnit 5**, **Mockito** (`@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)`)
- **Awaitility** — async assertions
- **JaCoCo** — coverage enforcement
